# .auditignore — known false-positive suppression for scripts/audit.sh
#
# Format: one `<file>:<line>` per line. Optional trailing comment
# after whitespace. Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are
# ignored. Substring match — file:line is the minimum specificity.
#
# Prune periodically: when a flagged line moves (file edits shift
# line numbers) the suppression silently misses and the FP comes
# back, forcing re-review. That's the intended audit hygiene.
#
# Add a one-line reason per entry so the next operator (or future
# you) can understand whether the suppression still applies.

# (Profiling.tsx pprof-recipe suppression retired 2026-07-06 — the sample code
# now carries a "no document.hidden applies server-side" comment within the
# check's 5-line lookahead, so the awk pass clears it naturally and the entry
# can't go stale on line drift again.)
